Findings:¶

from the above correlation table we can see that house prices are in a very strong positive correlation with GNP, GDP, Population, No. of Working employees, and disposable personal income. This shows us that when there is a rise in these factors in the economy this raises the house prices.

There's a loose negative correlation of house prices with Unemployment Rate, Income after mortgage paid and federal funds effective rate, this shows us that when there's a rise in economy of these factors, it affects the price negatively hence making the prices go down of houses.
